{"title_page": "2009 Virginia House of Delegates election", "text_new": "{{Citations missing|date=August 2009}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2009 Virginia House of Delegates election\n| country = Virginia\n| type = legislative\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 2007 Virginia House of Delegates election\n| previous_year = 2007\n| election_date = November 3, 2009\n| next_election = 2011 Virginia House of Delegates election\n| next_year = 2011\n| seats_for_election = All 100 seats in the [[Virginia House of Delegates]]\n| majority_seats = 51\n| turnout = 40.4%<ref>{{cite web|title=Registration/Turnout Statistics|url=https://www.elections.virginia.gov/resultsreports/registration-statistics/registrationturnout-statistics/index.html|publisher=Virginia Department of Elections|accessdate=January 24, 2018}}</ref> {{increase}}\n| image1 = [[File:Bill Howell, Speaker of the Virginia House of Delegates (Republican).png|160x160px]]\n| leader1 = [[William J. Howell|Bill Howell]]\n| leader_since1 = January 8, 2003\n| party1 = Republican Party (United States)\n| leaders_seat1 = [[Virginia's 28th House of Delegates district|28th]]\n| last_election1 = '''53'''\n| seats1 = '''59'''\n| seat_change1 = {{increase}} 6\n| popular_vote1 = '''1,047,069'''\n| percentage1 = '''56.8%'''\n| swing1 = {{increase}} 5.8%\n| title = [[List of Speakers of the Virginia House of Delegates|Speaker]]\n| before_election = [[William J. Howell|Bill Howell]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[William J. Howell|Bill Howell]]\n| after_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| image2 = [[File:Ward Armstrong podium.jpg|160x160px]]\n| leader2 = [[Ward Armstrong]]\n| party2 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| leader_since2 = February 24, 2007\n| leaders_seat2 = [[Virginia's 10th House of Delegates district|10th]]\n| last_election2 = 45\n| seats2 = 39\n| seat_change2 = {{decrease}} 6\n| popular_vote2 = 668,502\n| percentage2 = 36.2%\n| swing2 = {{decrease}} 6.7%\n| map_image          =\n| map_size           = 300px\n| map_alt            = \n| map_caption        = <big>'''Results:'''</big><br/>\n{{legend|#008|Democratic hold}}\n{{legend|#00f|Democratic gain}}\n{{legend|#800|Republican hold}}\n{{legend|#f00|Republican gain}}\n -->\n}}\n{{Elections in Virginia}}\n'''2009 Elections to the [[Virginia House of Delegates]]''' were held on November 3, 2009. Prior to the election, Republicans held 53 seats, Democrats held 43 seats, and Independents held 2 seats (both of whom caucus with the Republicans). \n\nThere were 2 seats previously held by Democrats that were vacant on election day: the 69th ([[Franklin P. Hall|Frank Hall]] resigned April 14, 2009) and the 80th ([[Kenneth R. Melvin|Ken Melvin]] resigned May 1, 2009). Eight incumbent Democrats were defeated, one incumbent Republican was defeated, and one open Republican seat was won by a Democrat. \n\nThe composition of the House of Delegates in 2010 was 59 Republicans, 2 Independents who caucus with the Republicans, and 39 Democrats.\n\n== Results ==\n\n=== Overview ===\n<ref>https://www.elections.virginia.gov/resultsreports/election-results/</ref> \n{| style=\"width:60%; text-align:center;\"\n|+\u2193\n|- style=\"color:white;\"\n| style=\"background:red; width:59.0%;\" |59\n| style=\"background:blue; width:39.0%;\" |39\n| style=\"background:grey; width:2.0%;\" |2\n|-\n|<span style=\"color:red;\">'''Republican'''</span>\n|<span style=\"color:blue;\">'''Democratic'''</span>\n\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Parties\n! rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Candidates\n! colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Seats\n! colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Popular Vote\n|-\n! align=\"center\" |2007\n! align=\"center\" |2009\n! align=\"center\" |+/-\n! align=\"center\" |Strength\n! align=\"center\" |Vote\n! align=\