\n|\n|\n|-\n|16\n|[[Forward (association football)|FW]]\n|{{flagicon|ARG}}\n|[[Nicol\u00e1s Benegas]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|25\n|[[Forward (association football)|FW]]\n|{{flagicon|ARG}}\n|[[Andr\u00e9s Ch\u00e1vez]]\n|2\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|'''2'''\n|\n|\n|-\n|34\n|[[Forward (association football)|FW]]\n|{{flagicon|ARG}}\n|[[Sebasti\u00e1n Palacios]]\n|2\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|1\n|\n|\n|'''3'''\n|\n|\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''Total'''\n|'''38'''\n|\n|'''1'''\n|'''3'''\n|\n|\n|'''26'''\n|\n|\n|'''67'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''1'''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar// Club Atl\u00e9tico Boca Juniors official web site] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{Boca Juniors seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2016 Club Atletico Boca Juniors season}}\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico Boca Juniors seasons]]\n[[Category:Argentine football clubs 2016 season]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n|club          = [[Boca Juniors]]\n|season        = 2016\n|chairman      = {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Daniel Angelici]]\n|chrtitle      = President\n|manager       = {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Rodolfo Arruabarrena]]<br /><small>(until February 29)</small><br />{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Guillermo Barros Schelotto]]<br /><small>(from March 2)</small>\n|stadium       = [[Estadio Alberto J. Armando|Estadio Alberto J. Armando <br /> (La Bombonera)]]\n|league        = [[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n|league result = [[2016 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|10th]]\n|cup2          = [[Supercopa Argentina]]\n|cup2 result   = [[2015 Supercopa Argentina|Runners-up]]\n|cup3          = [[Copa Libertadores]]\n|cup3 result   = ''[[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages#Semifinals|Semifinals]]''\n|league topscorer   = [[Carlos Tevez]] (4)\n|season topscorer   = [[Carlos Tevez]] (9)\n|highest attendance = \n|lowest attendance  = \n|average attendance = 32,197<ref>http://www.larojadeportes.cl/por-lejos-la-u-es-el-club-con-mas-promedio-de-publico-en-chile/</ref> (highest average attendance in the league in 2016)\n|pattern_la1 = _left\n|pattern_b1  = _Boca Juniors 2016 Uniforme Titular\n|pattern_ra1 = _right\n|pattern_sh1 = \n|pattern_so1 = \n|leftarm1    = 0000BD\n|body1       = 0000BD\n|rightarm1   = 0000BD\n|shorts1     = 0000BD\n|socks1      = 0000BD\n|pattern_la2 = _Boca Juniors 2016 Uniforme Suplente\n|pattern_b2  = _Boca Juniors 2016 Uniforme Suplente\n|pattern_ra2 = _Boca Juniors 2016 Uniforme Suplente\n|pattern_sh2 = \n|pattern_so2 = \n|leftarm2    = FFDF00\n|body2       = FFDF00\n|rightarm2   = FFDF00\n|shorts2     = FFDF00\n|socks2      = FFDF00\n|pattern_la3 = _Boca Juniors 2016 Tercer Uniforme\n|pattern_b3  = _Boca Juniors 2016 Tercer Uniforme\n|pattern_ra3 = _Boca Juniors 2016 Tercer Uniforme\n|pattern_sh3 = \n|pattern_so3 = \n|leftarm3    = 010101\n|body3       = 010101\n|rightarm3   = 010101\n|shorts3     = 010101\n|socks3      = 010101\n|prevseason = [[2015 Club Atl\u00e9tico Boca Juniors season|2015]]\n|nextseason = [[2016\u201317 Club Atl\u00e9tico Boca Juniors season|2016\u201317]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2016 Club Atl\u00e9tico Boca Juniors season''' is the 87th consecutive [[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] season for the senior squad. During the first part of the 2016, Boca Juniors will take part in the [[2016 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]], [[2015 Supercopa Argentina|Supercopa Argentina]] and in the [[2016 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]].\n\n==Season overview==\n===November===\nBoca played two friendly games, the first one against [[Puebla F.C.]] in [[Mexico]] losing 1-0 on November 19 and the second one in [[Resistencia, Chaco|Resistencia]] against a team of Liga Chaque\u00f1a de f\u00fatbol winning 3-2 on November 28.\n\n===December===\nIn the first days of December the new uniform was presented: it featured a lighter blue tone.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/nueva-camiseta |title=Camiseta Modelo 2016. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> Also, [[Daniel Angelici]] won the president elections and will be the chairman until 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/elecciones-boca-2015 |title=Angelici, presidente por cuatro a\u00f1os mas. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> On December 22 Boca were drawn into [[2016 Copa Libertadores second stage#Group 3|Group 3]] of the [[2016 Copa Libertadores]] with [[Bolivia]]n champions [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]], [[Categor\u00eda Primera A|Colombian]] champions [[Deportivo Cali]] and a team from the [[2016 Copa Libertadores first stage|First Stage]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/22122015-2254/la-copa-bridgestone-libertadores-toma-forma-tras-un-emocionante-sorteo |title=La Copa Bridgestone Libertadores toma forma tras un emocionante sorteo. |publisher=[[Confederaci\u00f3n Sudamericana de F\u00fatbol|Conmebol]] }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> On December 29 [[Jonathan Cristian Silva|Jonathan Silva]] was loaned from [[Sporting CP]] of Portugal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/silva-sporting |title=Silva, Primer refuerzo para 2016. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> In the last days of December [[Luciano Fabi\u00e1n Monz\u00f3n]] and [[Jos\u00e9 Pedro Fuenzalida]] left the club.\n\n===January===\nIn the first days of 2016 [[Leonardo Jara]] arrived from [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes (LP)]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/conferencia-jarasilva |title=Presentaci\u00f3n en sociedad. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> Also, [[Federico Carrizo]] and [[Luciano Acosta]] returned from their loans in [[Cruz Azul]] and [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes (LP)]]. Additionally, [[Nahuel Z\u00e1rate]] and [[Claudio P\u00e9rez]] also returned from their loans in [[Godoy Cruz Antonio Tomba|Godoy Cruz]] and [[Belgrano de C\u00f3rdoba|Belgrano]], but they will not be taken into consideration by Arruabarrena. P\u00e9rez rescinded his contract with Boca. Youth exponents [[Tom\u00e1s Pochettino]] and [[Franco Cristaldo]] signed for [[Defensa y Justicia]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/378 |title=Arranc\u00f3 la pretemporada 2016 con caras nuevas. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Defensa y Justicia }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> on an 18-month loan and for [[Elche CF]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elchecf.es/noticia/cristaldo-vengo-a-aprender-en-una-categoria-muy-dificil-y-un-futbol-diferente |title=Cristaldo: \"Vengo a aprender en una categor\u00eda muy dif\u00edcil y un f\u00fatbol diferente\". |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Elche CF }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> on a 6-month loan respectively. [[Daniel Osvaldo]] was officially presented again in Boca after playing in [[FC Porto]], he signed an 18-month contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/osvaldo-conferencia |title=Presentacion Daniel Osvaldo. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> [[Juan Cruz Komar]] signed for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Talleres (C\u00f3rdoba)|Talleres (C)]] on a six-month loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clubtalleres.com.ar/juan-cruz-komar-llega-a-talleres-para-reforzar-la-defensa/ |title=Juan Cruz Komar llega a Talleres para reforzar la defensa. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Talleres de C\u00f3rdoba }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> On January 12 [[Jonathan Calleri]] was sold to [[Deportivo Maldonado]] and loaned to [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.planetabocajuniors.com.ar/calleri-firmo-con-deportivo-maldonado/ |title=Calleri firm\u00f3 con Deportivo Maldonado. |publisher=Planeta Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> On January 16, Boca won 3-0 over [[Club Sport Emelec|Emelec]] in [[San Juan Province, Argentina|San Juan]], but then lost four friendlies including both against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]], leaving a bad picture of summer. This led to two new players arrive at the club: [[Frank Fabra]] and [[Juan Manuel Insaurralde]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/Insaurralde-refuerzo |title=De nuevo en casa. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n===February===\nIn earlier February, [[Leandro Mar\u00edn]] signed for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Tigre|Tigre]] on a six-month loan<ref>{{cite web |url=http://catigre.com.ar/practica-jueves-04-02-y-concentrados-vs-argentinos-jrs/ |title=Concentrados primera fecha. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Tigre }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> and [[Lisandro Magall\u00e1n]] signed for [[Defensa y Justicia]] also on a six-month loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/399 |title=Se incorporaron los hermanos Magall\u00e1n. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Defensa y Justicia }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> At the start of the tournament Boca played against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Temperley|Temperley]] in a 0-0 draw and four days later, lost against [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]] 0-4 in the [[2015 Supercopa Argentina]]. [[Nahuel Z\u00e1rate]] was loaned 18 months to [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe|Uni\u00f3n]] and [[Luciano Acosta]] to [[D.C. United]] until the end of 2016;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dcunited.com/post/2016/02/15/dc-united-acquire-luciano-acosta-boca-juniors |title=D.C. United acquire Luciano Acosta from Boca Juniors. |publisher=D.C. United Official Website }}</ref> also, [[Federico Bravo]] was loaned to [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] team [[New York City FC]] until the end of 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nycfc.com/post/2016/02/20/new-york-city-fc-acquire-federico-bravo |title=New York City FC Acquire Federico Bravo. |publisher=New York City FC Official Website }}</ref> On the second round of Primera Divisi\u00f3n Boca lost against [[Atl\u00e9tico Tucum\u00e1n]] 0-1, playing very bad. After six matches without scoring, Boca managed to win against [[San Mart\u00edn de San Juan|San Mart\u00edn (SJ)]] 1-0 on the third round of Primera Divisi\u00f3n, and against [[Newell's Old Boys]] 4-1 in Round 4. On February 24 Boca played the first match of [[2016 Copa Libertadores second stage#Group 3|the group stage]] of Copa Libertadores against [[Deportivo Cali]] drawing 0-0. On the round 5 of Primera Divisi\u00f3n Boca lost 0-1 against [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]].\n\n===March===\n[[Rodolfo Arruabarrena]] was sacked and is no longer the head coach of Boca; where he won 2 titles and managed 75 games, winning 47, drawing 13 and losing 15.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/conferencia-angelici-vasco |title=\"Siempre le estar\u00e9 agradecido a Boca\". |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> On March 1, [[Guillermo Barros Schelotto]] was announced as the new manager,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/conferencia-presentacion-guillermo |title=\"Trataremos de dar lo mejor\". |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> being his third time as manager in a professional football team. He returns to the club after his step as player between 1997 and 2007 where he won 16 titles. In the first match of the new manager, Boca played against [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]] in a 0-0 draw on the second round of Copa Libertadores Group Stage. On the Round 6, Boca played against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]], the [[Supercl\u00e1sico]], the most important match of [[Argentina]]; it was a 0-0 draw. Boca achieved another draw in the group stage of Copa Libertadores, 1-1 in [[La Paz]] against [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]]. On March 14 Boca managed to win 2-1 against [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe|Uni\u00f3n]]. On March 20 Boca lost the match 0-2 against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Lan\u00fas|Lan\u00fas]] playing very bad.\n\n===April===\nThe first match of April was a 3-0 victory over [[Atl\u00e9tico de Rafaela]]. On April 4 the third uniform was presented: it is black with a golden strip.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bocajuniors.com.ar/el-club/camiseta-Boca |title=De estreno. |publisher=P\u00e1gina Oficial Boca Juniors }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> Boca won the first match in Copa Libertadores: 3-1 against [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]] on the fourth match of the group. On April 10 Boca lost the match 0-2 against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Tigre|Tigre]]. On April 13 Boca qualified to the [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages|final stages]] of the Copa Libertadores after winning 1-0 in [[Avellaneda]] against [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]]. In the 11 round Boca won 4-1 against [[Aldosivi]]. Boca finished the Group Stage of Copa Libertadores winning 6-2 against [[Deportivo Cali]]. The second [[Superclasico]] against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]] was another 0-0 draw. In the first game of the [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages#Round of 16|Round of 16]] of Copa Libertadores, Boca achieved a great victory 2-1 in [[Asunci\u00f3n]] against [[Cerro Porte\u00f1o]]. In the round 13 of the local Tournament Boca lost 1-0 against [[Argentinos Juniors]], playing with an alternative team.\n\n===May===\nIn the second leg of the [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages#Round of 16|Round of 16]] of Copa Libertadores, Boca won 3-1 against [[Cerro Porte\u00f1o]] and advanced to the [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages#Quarterfinals|Quarterfinals]]. In the round 14 of the local tournament Boca played against [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Hurac\u00e1n|Hurac\u00e1n]] in a 0-0 draw. In the first leg of the Copa Libertadores [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages#Quarterfinals|Quarterfinals]] played on May 12, Boca tied 1-1 in [[Montevideo]] against [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]]. On May 15, Boca played against [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes (LP)]] and lost 3-1. On May 19 Boca advanced to the [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages#Semifinals|Semifinals]] of the Copa Libertadores after beating [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]] in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|Penalty shoot-out]]. Boca played the last match of the local tournament and the season: it was a 0-0 draw against [[Defensa y Justicia]].\n\n==Current squad==\n\n:''Last updated on May 22, 2016''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; font-size:80%; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Squad No.\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Name\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Nationality\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Position\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Date of Birth (Age)\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Apps\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Goals\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Signed from\n! style=\"background:#00009B; color:gold; text-align:center;\"| Note\n|-\n! colspan=\"9\"  style=\"background:#dcdcdc; text-align:center;\"| Goalkeepers\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Agust\u00edn Orion]] ''([[Captain (association football)|VC 4\u00ba]])''\n| {{flagicon|Argentina}}\n| [[Goalkeeper (association football)|GK]]\n| {{Birth date and age|1981|6|26}}\n|200\n| -163\n| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes (LP)]]\n|\n|-\n| 23\n| [[Ramiro Mart\u00ednez (footballer)|Ramiro Mart\u00ednez]]\n| {{flagicon|Argentina}}\n| [[Goalkeeper (association football)|GK]]\n| {{Birth date and age|1991|4|18}}\n|0\n|0\n|{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Boca Juniors Reserves and Academy|Academy]]\n|\n|-\n| 31\n| [[Guillermo Sara]]\n| {{flagicon|Argentina}}\n| [[Goalkeeper (association football)|GK]]\n| {{Birth date and age|1987|9|30}}\n|19\n| -17\n| {{flagicon|SPA}} [[Real Betis]]\n|\n|-\n! colspan=\"9\"  style=\"background:#dcdcdc; text-align:center;\"| Defenders\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Daniel D\u00edaz]] ''([[Captain (association football)|C]])''