 song of world's loneliest whale\n| work = EarthSky\n| url = http://earthsky.org/earth/52-hertz-song-of-worlds-loneliest-whale\n| accessdate = 2012-09-23\n}}\n</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Anderson\">\n{{cite web\n| last = Anderson\n| first = Ben\n| date = 2011-01-05\n| title = 'World's loneliest whale' pays visit to Alaska\n| publisher = Alaska Dispatch\n| url = http://www.alaskadispatch.com/article/worlds-loneliest-whale-pays-visit-alaska\n| accessdate = 2012-11-17\n}}\n</ref>\n\n<ref name=Cornell>\n{{cite web\n |work=Bioacoustics Research Program\n |publisher=The Cornell Lab of Ornithology\n |url=http://www.birds.cornell.edu/brp/listen-to-project-sounds/blue-whale\n |title=Blue Whale\n |accessdate=2015-02-13\n |url-status=dead\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226002906/http://www.birds.cornell.edu/brp/listen-to-project-sounds/blue-whale\n |archive-date=2015-02-26\n}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite journal||first=William A.|last=Watkins|first2=Mary Ann|last2=Daher|first3=Gina M.|last3=Reppucci|first4=Joseph E.|last4=George|first5=Darel L.|last5=Martin|first6=Nancy A.|last6=DiMarzio|first7=Damon P.|last7=Gannon|date=2000|title=Seasonality and distribution of whale calls in the North Pacific|journal=Oceanography|volume=13|issue=1|pages=62\u201367|doi=10.5670/oceanog.2000.54|url=https://tos.org/oceanography/assets/docs/13-1_watkins.pdf|access-date=2020-02-18|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190429193056/https://tos.org/oceanography/assets/docs/13-1_watkins.pdf|archive-date=2019-04-29}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.whoi.edu/cms/images/oceanus/2005/5/v44n1-briefs12en_10079.jpg Map of the 52-hertz whale's migration patterns]\n\n[[Category:Individual cetaceans]]\n[[Category:Mysteries]]\n[[Category:Pacific Ocean]]\n[[Category:Sound measurements]]\n[[Category:Whale sounds]]\n[[Category:Unexplained phenomena]]\n", "name_user": "Modulus12", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adjusted links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/