es Ronald Fisher (IG) 19.1%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 50th House of Delegates district|50th]]\n| Jackson Miller\n| Republican\n| 2006\n| Reelected\n| '''Jackson Miller (R) 60.4%''' <BR> Jeanette Rishell (D) 39.5%\n|- {{party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[Virginia's 51st House of Delegates district|51st]]\n| bgcolor = \"lightgrey\" | Michele McQuigg\n| Republican\n| 1997\n| Elected to Clerk of Court\n| '''[[Paul F. Nichols|Paul Nichols]] (D) 51.8%''' <br /> Faisal Gill (R) 47.7%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 52nd House of Delegates district|52nd]]\n| Jeff Frederick\n| Republican\n| 2003\n| Reelected\n| '''Jeff Frederick (R) 58.6%''' <BR> Christopher Brown (D) 41.2%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 54th House of Delegates district|54th]]\n| Bobby Orrock\n| Republican\n| 1989\n| Reelected\n| '''Bobby Orrock (R) 73.7%''' <BR> Kimbra Kincheloe (I) 26.2%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 56th House of Delegates district|56th]]\n| Bill Janis\n| Republican\n| 2001\n| Reelected\n| '''Bill Janis (R) 65.9%''' <BR> Will Shaw (D) 34.0%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 59th House of Delegates district|59th]]\n| Watkins Abbitt\n| Independent\n| 1985\n| Reelected\n| '''Watkins Abbitt (I) 60.2%''' <BR> Connie Brennan (D) 39.7%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 67th House of Delegates district|67th]]\n| Chuck Caputo\n| Democratic\n| 2005\n| Reelected\n| '''Chuck Caputo (D) 52.7%''' <BR> Marc Cadin (R) 47.3%\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| [[Virginia's 68th House of Delegates district|68th]]\n| Katherine Waddell\n| Independent\n| 2005\n| Defeated\n| '''Manoli Loupassi (R) 54.1%''' <BR> Katherine Waddell (I) 42.1% <BR> Bill Grogan (I) 3.7%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 69th House of Delegates district|69th]]\n| Frank Hall\n| Democratic\n| 1975\n| Reelected\n| '''Frank Hall (D) 82.8%''' <BR> Ray Gargiulo (R) 17.0%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 72nd House of Delegates district|72nd]]\n| bgcolor = \"lightgrey\" | Jack Reid\n| Republican\n| 1989\n| Retired\n| '''Jimmie Massie (R) 67.2%''' <BR> Tom Herbert (D) 32.7%\n|-\n| [[Virginia's 78th House of Delegates district|78th]]\n| 