was held on Tuesday, November 4.\n\n==Election results==\n\n=== Overview ===\n<ref>https://www.elections.virginia.gov/resultsreports/election-results/</ref>\n{| style=\"width:60%; text-align:center;\"\n|+\u2193\n|- style=\"color:white;\"\n| style=\"background:red; width:61.0%;\" |61\n| style=\"background:blue; width:37.0%;\" |37\n| style=\"background:grey; width:2.0%;\" |2\n|-\n|<span style=\"color:red;\">'''Republican'''</span>\n|<span style=\"color:blue;\">'''Democratic'''</span>\n\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Parties\n! rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Candidates\n! colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Seats\n! colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" |Popular Vote\n|-\n! align=\"center\" |2001\n! align=\"center\" |2003\n! align=\"center\" |+/-\n! align=\"center\" |Strength\n! align=\"center\" |Vote\n! align=\"center\" |%\n! align=\"center\" |Change\n|-\n{{party color|Republican Party (United States)}}\n| align=\"left\" |[[Republican Party of Virginia|Republican]]\n| align=\"right\" |74\n| align=\"right\" {{party shading/Republican}} |64\n| align=\"right\" {{party shading/Republican}} |61\n| align=\"right\" |{{decrease}} 3\n| align=\"right\" {{party shading/Republican}} |61.00%\n| align=\"right\" {{party shading/Republican}} |630,430\n| align=\"right\" {{party shading/Republican}} |57.85%\n| align=\"right\" |\n|-\n{{party color|Democratic Party (United States)}}\n| align=\"left\" |[[Democratic Party of Virginia|Democratic]]\n| align=\"right\" |57\n| align=\"right\" |34\n| align=\"right\" |37\n| align=\"right\" |{{increase}} 3\n| align=\"right\" |37.00%\n| align=\"right\" |403,531\n| align=\"right\" |37.03%\n| align=\"right\" |\n|-\n{{party color|Independent Party (United States)}}\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n| align=\"right\" |11\n| align=\"right\" |2\n| align=\"right\" |2\n| al